            . I live in Paddington-street, and am in the employ of <rs id="t18241202-142-viclabel796" type="occupation">Mr.</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18241202-142-victim904 t18241202-142-viclabel796"></join> Thomas Burchett. About five o'clock in the evening of the 6th of November, I was told that a shawl had been taken from the door. I went out, and saw the prisoner with it in his hand. I called Stop thief! and some persons stopped him before I lost sight of him. I saw him try to throw the shawl down.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18241202-142-person906">
                  WILLIAM 
                  PIKE
               <interp inst="t18241202-142-person906" type="surname" value="PIKE"></interp>
